  "prompt": "Which TV show is best ever?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" TV show ever is highly subjective and depends on individual tastes and preferences. However, here are some TV shows that are frequently cited as being among the best, according to critics and audiences:\n\n1. **\"The Sopranos\"** \u2013 Known for its complex characters and storytelling, it\u2019s often cited as one of the greatest TV dramas.\n2. **\"Breaking Bad\"** \u2013 Acclaimed for its writing, acting, and character development.\n3. **\"The Wire\"** \u2013 Praised for its realistic portrayal of urban life and social commentary.\n4. **\"Game of Thrones\"** \u2013 Despite some controversy over its final season, it is widely recognized for its epic storytelling and production value.\n5. **\"Friends\"** \u2013 A highly influential and beloved sitcom with a lasting cultural impact.\n6. **\"The Simpsons\"** \u2013 As the longest-running American sitcom and animated program, it\u2019s known for its cultural relevance and humor.\n7. **\"Mad Men\"** \u2013 Celebrated for its attention to historical detail and character depth.\n8. **\"Seinfeld\"** \u2013 Often referred to as a show \"about nothing,\" it changed the landscape of sitcoms with its unique humor.\n9. **\"M*A*S*H\"** \u2013 Remembered for blending comedy and drama during its run.\n10. **\"The Twilight Zone\"** \u2013 An anthology series known for its thought-provoking and often unsettling stories.\n\nUltimately, the best show is a matter of personal preference, so it\u2019s worth exploring different genres and styles to find what resonates most with you.",
